[size=4][b]BetterBots — Bot Combat Abilities for Solo Play[/b][/size]

Aims to bring VT2-level bot ability usage to Darktide. Covers stance, dash, charge, shout, and stealth abilities with smart per-ability trigger heuristics — item-based abilities (relics, shields) are experimental and grenades are planned.

Darktide has a complete bot ability system built into the behavior tree, but Fatshark hardcoded a whitelist that only allows two abilities. This mod removes that gate and injects the missing metadata so the existing infrastructure handles the rest.

[b]Solo Play only.[/b] Darktide uses dedicated servers — mods cannot affect gameplay on Fatshark's servers. This mod only works when you host locally via the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url] mod. It does [b]not[/b] work in public matchmaking or any other online mode.

[size=3][b]What works[/b][/size]

[b]Stance abilities (reliable):[/b]
[list]
[*]Veteran: Executioner's Stance / Voice of Command
[*]Psyker: Scrier's Gaze
[*]Ogryn: Point-Blank Barrage
[*]Arbites: Castigator's Stance
[*]Hive Scum: Enhanced Desperado / Rampage
[/list]

[b]Dash / shout / stealth abilities (reliable):[/b]
[list]
[*]Veteran: Infiltrate (stealth)
[*]Zealot: Fury of the Faithful (dash), Shroudfield (stealth)
[*]Ogryn: Bull Rush (charge), Loyal Protector (taunt)
[*]Psyker: Venting Shriek (shout)
[*]Arbites: Break the Line (charge)
[/list]

[b]Item-based abilities (experimental):[/b]
[list]
[*]Zealot: Bolstering Prayer (relic) — works well
[*]Psyker: Telekine Shield — works sometimes
[*]Arbites: Nuncio-Aquila — works sometimes
[/list]

[b]Smart trigger conditions (new in v0.2.0):[/b]
Bots use per-ability heuristics to decide [i]when[/i] to activate — based on enemy count, threat level, health/toughness, distance, and ally state. Each ability has specific activate and hold rules grounded in community tactics. 12 of 13 trigger functions validated in-game.

[size=3][b]What doesn't work yet[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Grenades / blitz abilities (different architecture needed)
[*]Hive Scum: Stimm Field (item-based, same challenge as above)
[/list]

[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/19]Darktide Mod Loader[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/8]Darktide Mod Framework (DMF)[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/183]Tertium 5[/url] or [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url] — recommended for non-veteran bot classes
[/list]

[size=3][b]Install[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Extract [font=Courier New]BetterBots.zip[/font] into your Darktide [font=Courier New]mods/[/font] folder
[*]Add [font=Courier New]BetterBots[/font] to [font=Courier New]mods/mod_load_order.txt[/font] (below [font=Courier New]dmf[/font])
[*]Re-patch mods
[/list]

[size=3][b]Verify[/b][/size]

Look for [font=Courier New]BetterBots loaded[/font] and [font=Courier New]injected meta_data for ...[/font] in game chat on mission start.

[size=3][b]Known limitations[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Psyker Scrier's Gaze can cause warp overcharge explosions (bot has no vent ability)
[*]Item-based abilities (force field, drone) have low success rates in sustained combat
[*]Mods are disabled after every Darktide update — re-patch required
[*]Hive Scum abilities are untested (DLC required)
[/list]

